{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01W2hdAPWRtb8iwNr2VUPxQ9","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile my comprehensive findings:\n\n## Summary: Run Grouping/Sorting Feature and Runs Page UI\n\nBased on my thorough search of the codebase, here are all the relevant files and components:\n\n### 1. Server-Side Run Grouping/Sorting Logic (Go)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\n**Core Function:** `groupAndSortRuns()` (lines 506-594)\n- Filters out \"list-tasks\" workflow runs\n- Builds parent-child relationships via `parentMap`\n- Sorts top-level runs: running first, then by `StartedAt` descending\n- Groups runs by `TaskID`, preserving sort order\n- Returns flat list of `apiGroupedEntry` objects suitable for both HTML and JSON\n\n**Key Data Structures:**\n\n1. **`apiGroupedEntry`** (lines 495-501) - Flat representation of grouped entry:\n   ```go\n   type apiGroupedEntry struct {\n       TaskHeader bool    `json:\"task_header,omitempty\"`\n       TaskID     string  `json:\"task_id,omitempty\"`\n       IsParent   bool    `json:\"is_parent,omitempty\"`\n       IsChild    bool    `json:\"is_child,omitempty\"`\n       Run        *apiRun `json:\"run,omitempty\"`\n   }\n   ```\n\n2. **`apiRun`** (lines 442-457) - API representation with all run fields:\n   - Includes `ParentRunID`, `TaskID` for grouping relationships\n   - Includes timing, state, container info\n\n**Handler Routes:**\n- `GET /runs` → `handleRunsList()` (line 255) - HTML page rendering\n- `GET /api/runs` → `handleAPIRuns()` (line 596) - JSON API endpoint\n\nBoth use `groupAndSortRuns()` to process runs before returning.\n\n---\n\n### 2. HTML Templates for Runs Page\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html`\n\n**Key Features:**\n- **Task Grouping Header** (line 35): `<tr class=\"run-task-header\"><td colspan=\"9\">Task: {{.TaskID}}</td></tr>`\n- **Run Rows** (lines 37-47):\n  - Regular rows for ungrouped runs\n  - `.IsChild` class for child runs (indented)\n  - `.IsParent` class for parent runs (dimmed)\n- **Polling/Updates** (lines 89-143): Client-side JS polls `/api/runs` every 3 seconds and dynamically renders grouped entries\n- **Project Filter** (lines 4-15): Dropdown to filter by project\n- **Container Cleanup** (line 13): Button to remove retained containers\n\n---\n\n### 3. Domain Types for Run Status\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n\n**RunState Enum** (lines 8-16):\n- `RunStatePending` = \"pending\"\n- `RunStateRunning` = \"running\"\n- `RunStateSucceeded` = \"succeeded\"\n- `RunStateFailed` = \"failed\"\n- `RunStateCancelled` = \"cancelled\"\n\n**Run Struct** (lines 31-48):\n- `TaskID` field: optional task ID for grouping runs\n- `ParentRunID` field: ID of parent (host) run for container runs\n- `IsHost` field: true for host workflow runs vs container runs\n- `WorkflowName`, `State`, `Title`, `ErrorMessage`, `ContainerID`, `BaseSHA`\n\n---\n\n### 4. Status Badge Rendering\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n\n**Badge Styling** (lines 107-127):\n- `.badge-pending`: Yellow background, brown text\n- `.badge-running`: Blue background with pulsing animation\n- `.badge-succeeded`: Green background\n- `.badge-failed`: Red background\n- `.badge-cancelled`: Gray background\n- `.badge-stopped`: Gray background\n\n**Run Tree Grouping CSS** (lines 575-604):\n- `.run-task-header`: Task section headers\n- `.run-parent-row`: Dimmed parent runs (opacity: 0.7)\n- `.run-child-row`: Indented child runs with \"└ \" prefix\n\n---\n\n### 5. Timing Display Logic\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\n**Functions:**\n- `formatRunTiming()` (line 1685): \"Running: 5m\" | \"Completed: 20m, 1 hour ago\" | \"Pending: empty\"\n- `formatSmartDuration()` (line 1624): Duration formatting (3s, 2m, 1h20m)\n- `roundRelativeTime()` (line 1642): Relative time with neat breakpoints\n- `formatTime()` (line 1601): ISO format timestamps\n- `formatDuration()` (line 1608): Duration between two times\n\n---\n\n### 6. Database Persistence\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`\n\n**Schema:**\n- Column: `task_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT ''` (line 85)\n- Stored in INSERT (line 136) and UPDATE (line 177) statements\n- Retrieved with SELECT via `runSelectCols` (line 145)\n\n---\n\n### 7. Tests\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go`\n\n**Test Coverage:**\n- Line 2080: `TaskHeader` validation\n- Line 2087: Task ID persistence verification\n- Lines 2112-2154: TaskID storage, persistence, and default empty handling\n\n---\n\n### 8. Related Configuration\n\n**Template Functions** (handler.go, lines 103-111):\n- `stateColor()` - Maps state to CSS class\n- `healthColor()` - Project health indicator color\n- `formatTime()`, `formatDuration()`, `formatRunTiming()` - Display helpers\n- `truncate()`, `shortContainerID()` - String formatting\n\n**Recent Commit:** `ed31df6` (Mar 13 2026)\n- Moved grouping/sorting from client-side JS to server-side Go\n- Eliminates visual \"jumping\" on initial page load\n- Both HTML and JSON API now receive pre-sorted/grouped entries\n\n---\n\n## File Paths (Absolute)\n\n1. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Core grouping/sorting logic\n2. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` - UI template\n3. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - Status styling\n4. `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run type definitions\n5. `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` - Database persistence\n6. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go` - Tests"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a0b425ce4a2047e1a (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 49828\ntool_uses: 27\nduration_ms: 54005</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2f5b3a10-2c53-4a3a-a212-5498e6e5d993","uuid":"ef848432-d83a-4728-af1d-